data.description: Solid brick home in the Lansdale Borough.   As you  enter the  home, you are welcomed with an enclosed front porch.  The spacious living room and dining room offer hardwood flooring  and high ceilings.  The kitchen boasts cherry cabinets, granite counters, stainless steel appliances and tile floor.  Off the kitchen is a large  three-season room offering additional living space. This leads to the patio overlooking the backyard.  There is also additional parking and a shed.  The second floor offers a large hall bath with  with granite vanity and tile flooring, spacious hall closet (or potential laundry room), and 2 nicely-sized bedrooms with hardwood flooring.  The third floor is a  spacious third bedroom or office.   Full basement offering laundry area and great storage space completes this home. Short walk to town, parks, shops and restaurants.  Minutes to the Lansdale train station, PA turnpike, routes 309 ad  202. Sellers would like a June 17th settlement if possible.
